  "prompt": "What is the best site to download books?",
  "response": "There are several websites where you can download books legally and for free. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg**: Offers over 60,000 free eBooks, mainly classic literature. [Project Gutenberg](https://www.gutenberg.org/)\n\n2. **Internet Archive**: A non-profit digital library that provides free access to millions of books, movies, music, and more. [Internet Archive](https://archive.org/)\n\n3. **Google Books**: Allows you to search and preview millions of books, and sometimes download free eBook versions. [Google Books](https://books.google.com/)\n\n4. **Open Library**: An initiative of the Internet Archive, providing access to millions of books. [Open Library](https://openlibrary.org/)\n\n5. **ManyBooks**: Offers more than 50,000 free eBooks available for download in various formats. [ManyBooks](https://manybooks.net/)\n\n6. **LibriVox**: Provides free audiobooks from the public domain, recorded by volunteers. [LibriVox](https://librivox.org/)\n\n7. **BookBub**: While mainly a site for discounted eBooks, it often highlights free eBooks as well. [BookBub](https://www.bookbub.com/)\n\nBefore downloading, always ensure that the site you\u2019re using has the proper authorization to distribute the book you're interested in to avoid any legal issues.",
